@startuml Use Case Diagram
left to right direction
skinparam packageStyle rectangle

title COLORS Web Application - Use Case Diagram

actor "User" as user

rectangle "COLORS Web Application" {
    usecase "Login" as UC1
    usecase "Logout" as UC2
    usecase "Add Color" as UC3
    usecase "Search Colors" as UC4
    usecase "View Color Results" as UC5
    usecase "Manage Session\n(Cookie)" as UC6
}

database "MySQL\nDatabase" as db

user --> UC1
user --> UC2
user --> UC3
user --> UC4

UC4 ..> UC5 : <<include>>
UC1 ..> UC6 : <<include>>
UC2 ..> UC6 : <<include>>

UC1 --> db
UC3 --> db
UC4 --> db

note right of UC1
  User enters login credentials.
  System validates against Users table.
  On success, a session cookie is saved
  and user is redirected to color.html.
end note

note right of UC3
  Authenticated user enters a color name.
  System inserts the color into the
  Colors table linked to the user.
end note

note right of UC4
  Authenticated user enters a search term.
  System queries Colors table using
  LIKE pattern matching for the user.
end note

@enduml
